dmired by Robespierre and Thomas Jefferson. Written from different, even opposing perspectives, these lucid essays convey a sense of the vital and contentious debate surrounding Rousseau and his legacy.For this edition Susan Dunn has provided a new translation of the Discourse on the Sciences and Arts and has revised a previously published translation of The Social Contract.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCivilizationvEarly works to 1800. 0aCivilizationxEarly works to 1800. 0aPolitical sciencevEarly works to 1800. 0aPolitical sciencexEarly works to 1800. 0aSocial contractvEarly works to 1800. 0aSocial contractxEarly works to 1800. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aBellah, Robert N.1 aBellah, Robert N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBromwich, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBromwich, David.1 aDunn, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDunn, Susan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMay, Gita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMay, Gita.1 aO'Brien, Conor Cruise.1 aO’Brien, Conor Cruise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030012943440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300129434423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300129434/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles